      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "As a consequence of the precipitation, the likelihood of moist and wet avalanches being released will increase gradually. The avalanche danger should be investigated very thoroughly in the relevant locality. The avalanche prone locations are to be found in particular at the base of rock walls, and adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. Places where weaknesses exist in the old snowpack are especially precarious. The avalanches can be released in deep layers of the snowpack. Gliding avalanches can also occur.",
        "highlights": "In regions exposed to heavier precipitation the avalanche prone locations are more widespread."
